  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "a. An introductory workshop with all  relevant technical and policy actors  within the country – during this  workshop, the technical team, which  will implement the process through  support from UN-Habitat and European  Commission teams will be identified and  introduced to the analytical aspects of  DEGURBA.  b. Technical advisory workshops – which  will constitute two on-the-job trainings  and work-sessions, in which local data  will be directly used to implement  DEGURBA, and SDG 11 computation  methodologies introduced and directly  implemented for select cities with local  data.  c. Continuous virtual support – which will  include virtual working sessions with the  technical teams on a-need-basis over  a period of one and half years (and/or  as long as required). This support will  range from implementation of DEGURBA  and NUA/SDG 11 workflows to data  interpretation and reporting guidance."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
